        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 15. Pupa of Thiotricha gemmulans Meyrick, 1931. A, Head and thorax, dorsal view. Arrow indicates many minute granular projections on vertex; B, Abdomen, ventral view. Arrow indicates an oval pad equipped with a row of spines and A10 with triangular projections; C, A7, dorsal view. Arrow indicates a transverse row of tergal spinules on both anterior and caudal margins; D, A7, lateral view. Arrow indicates an oval pad equipped with a row of spines and rows of tergal spines. Scale bar: 0.40 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4889160/files/figure.png" .

